com.googlecode.objectify
Class ObjectifyImpl

java.lang.Object
  com.googlecode.objectify.ObjectifyImpl
All Implemented Interfaces:
Objectify
public class ObjectifyImpl
extends java.lang.Object
implements Objectify

Implementation of the Objectify interface. Note we *always* use the DatastoreService methods that use transactions to avoid the confusion of implicit transactions.

Author:
Jeff Schnitzer

get in interface Objectify

put

public com.google.appengine.api.datastore.Key put(java.lang.Object obj)
Description copied from interface: Objectify
Just like the DatastoreService method, but uses your typed object. If the object has a null key, one will be created. If the object has a key, it will overwrite any value formerly stored with that key.

Specified by:
put in interface Objectify
See Also:

put

public java.util.List<com.google.appengine.api.datastore.Key> put(java.lang.Iterable<?> objs)
Description copied from interface: Objectify
Just like the DatastoreService method, but uses your typed objects. If any of the objects have a null key, one will be created. If any of the objects has a key, it will overwrite any value formerly stored with that key. You can mix and match the types of objects stored.

prepare

public <T> ObPreparedQuery<T> prepare(ObQuery query)
Description copied from interface: Objectify

Prepares a query for execution. The resulting ObjPreparedQuery allows the result set to be iterated through in a typesafe way.

You should create a query by calling one of the ObjectifyFactory.createQuery() methods.

Note: If Query is keysOnly, result will be ObjPreparedQuery. This behavior differs from how the underlying DatastoreService works.

Specified by:
prepare in interface Objectify
See Also:
DatastoreService.prepare(Query)

getTxn

public com.google.appengine.api.datastore.Transaction getTxn()
Description copied from interface: Objectify

Note that this is *not* the same as DatastoreService.getCurrentTransaction(), which uses implicit transaction management. Objectify does not use implicit (thread local) transactions.

Specified by:
getTxn in interface Objectify
Returns:
the transaction associated with this Objectify instance, or null if no transaction is associated with this instance.

getDatastore

public com.google.appengine.api.datastore.DatastoreService getDatastore()
Specified by:
getDatastore in interface Objectify
Returns:
the underlying DatastoreService implementation so you can work with Entity objects if you so choose. Also allows you to allocateIds or examine thread local transactions.
